Quote:  The Rangiatea Church is being renovated, i hear, and the School of Art has been asked to reconstruct the arapaki work. it is i believe all poutama, and kakaho work, the real thing. We have assembled a lot of kakaho at Rotorua, material much cheaper than mock kakaho, but a little more difficult to handle.
